{
  "text": "c-myc protein is a transcription factor which participates in most aspects of cellular function, including replication, growth, metabolism, differentiation, and apoptosis [CITATION_1] . Most, if not all, types of human malignancy have been reported to have amplification and/or overexpression of c-myc oncogene.",
